<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3675] hbase.hlog.split.skip.errors is false by default but we don&apos;t act properly when its true; can make for inconsistent view</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3675</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;So, by default hbase.hlog.split.skip.error is false so we should not be skipping errors (What should we do, abort?).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyways, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3674&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3674&lt;/a&gt;.  It has checksum error on near to last log BUT it writes out recovered.edits  gotten so far.  We then go and assign the regions anyways, applying edits gotten so far, though there are edits behind the checksum error still to be recovered.  Not good.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12501847">HBASE-3675</key>
            <summary>hbase.hlog.split.skip.errors is false by default but we don&apos;t act properly when its true; can make for inconsistent view</summary>
